hopobject.body: Languages digestivemeds.com The researchers defined binge drinking as five or more drinks for both men and women. (It's also sometimes defined as five drinks for men and four for women during a two-hour period.) A drink was 12 ounces of beer, four ounces of wine, 12-ounce wine cooler, a mixed drink or shot glass of liquor. The historical highs for binge drinking were the late '70s and early '80s, when about 40% reported binge drinking, she says.
